HEADWORD: Encyclopedical
<hw>En*cy`clo*ped"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>encyclop⟦eacute⟧dique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining
to, or of the nature of, an encyclopedia; broad in scope or content;
embracing a wide range of subjects; <as>as, a person having
<ex>encyclopedic</ex> knowledge of a subject</as>.</def> <altsp>[Also
spelled <asp>encyclopaedic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encyclopedism</ent>⟦br⟧
